wling FanSided] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824012648/https://fansided.com/fandom250/harry-potter-jk-rowling/ |date=2017-08-24 }} on ''Harry Potter'': \"The success of the books \u2014 every one of which has sold over 65 million copies \u2014 and the films \u2014 which have done billions of dollars worth of box office sales worldwide \u2014 is perhaps the easiest way to demonstrate the sheer size of the Harry Potter fandom.\" (November 2016)</ref>||[[fantasy]]\n|-\n|''[[Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire]]'' || [[J. K. Rowling]] || English || 2000 || 65 million<ref name=\"fansided.com\"/>||[[fantasy]]\n|-\n|''[[Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix]]'' || [[J. K. Rowling]] || English || 2003 || 65 million<ref name=\"fansided.com\"/>||[[fantasy]]\n|-\n|''[[Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince]]'' || [[J. K. Rowling]] || English || 2005 || 65 million<ref name=\"fansided.com\"/>||[[fantasy]]\n|-\n|''[[Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows]]'' || [[J. K. Rowling]] || English || 2007 || 65 million<ref name=\"fansided.com\"/>||[[fantasy]]\n|-\n|''[[The Catcher in the Rye]]'' || [[J. D. Salinger]] || English || 1951 || 65 million||[[Coming-of-age story|coming-of-age]]\n|-style=\"background-color:lavender;\"\n|-\n|''[[The Bridges of Madison County]]'' || [[Robert James Waller]] || English || 1992 || 60 million<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://triblive.com/aande/theaterarts/9886121-74/county-bridges-stanley|title='The Bridges of Madison County' novel springs to life as a musical|last=Carter|first=Alice T.|website=TribLIVE.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-04-13|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170414082053/http://triblive.com/aande/theaterarts/9886121-74/county-bridges-stanley|archivedate=2017-04-14}}</ref>|| [[romance novel|romance]]\n|-\n|''[[Ben-Hur: A Tale of the Christ]]''\n|[[Lew Wallace]]\n|English\n|1880\n|50 million<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thesouthern.com/lifestyles/ben-hur-a-tale-of-the-christ/image_8afcb387-fe15-55