aise |title=D\u00e9couvertes Gallimard ou la culture encyclop\u00e9dique \u00e0 la fran\u00e7aise |author=Fran\u00e7oise Hache-Bissette |website=ricochet-jeunes.org |year=2002 |accessdate=15 October 2017 |language=fr |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170921144648/https://www.ricochet-jeunes.org/articles/decouvertes-gallimard-ou-la-culture-encyclopedique-la-francaise |archivedate=21 September 2017 }}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Redwall]]'' || [[Brian Jacques]] || English || 22 || 1986\u20132011 || 20 million<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailyprincetonian.com/2009/05/08/23661/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-08-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100914062331/http://www.dailyprincetonian.com/2009/05/08/23661/ |archivedate=2010-09-14 }} on ''Redwall'': \"Brian Jacques\u2019 award-winning books, which have sold more than 20 million copies worldwide in 28 languages.\" (8 May 2009)</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Maisy Mouse|Maisy]]'' || [[Lucy Cousins]] || English || 23 || 1990\u2013present || 20 million<ref name=rjmlicensing />\n|-\n|''[[Dragonlance]]'' || Various authors || English || more than 150 || 1984\u2013present || 20 million<ref>[http://www.iesb.net/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=4260&Itemid=99 IESB.net] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081024031858/http://www.iesb.net/index.php?option=com_content |date=2008-10-24 }} (4 February 2008)</ref>\n|-\n|\u5e7b\u9b54\u5927\u6226 (''[[Genma Taisen]]'') || [[Kazumasa Hirai (author)|Kazumasa Hirai]] || Japanese || 20 || 1979\u20131983 || 20 million<ref>[http://plusd.itmedia.co.jp/mobile/articles/0504/04/news072.html IT Media Mobile] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090922125256/http://plusd.itmedia.co.jp/mobile/articles/0504/04/news072.html |date=2009-09-22 }} (4 April 2005)</ref>\n|-\n|\u9752\u6625\u306e\u9580 (''[[The Gate of Youth (novel)|The Gate of Youth]]'') || [[Hiroyuki Itsuki]] || Japanese ||  || 1970\u2013present || 20 million<ref>\n[http://search.japantimes.co.jp/cgi-bin/fd20050320cs.html The Japan Times] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090110042028/http://search.japantimes.co.jp/cgi-bin/fd20050320cs.html |date=2009-01-10 }} (20 March 2005)</ref>\n|-\n|\u30b9\u30ec\u30a4\u30e4\u30fc\u30ba (''[[Slayers]]'') || [[Hajime Kanzaka]] || Japanese || 50 || 1989\u2013present || 20{{nbsp}}million<ref>{{cite news |last1=Komatsu |first1=Mikikazu |title=Slayers Novel Original Series' Long-Awaited 16th Volume Set for Release on October 20 |url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2018/08/31/slayers-novel-original-series-long-awaited-16th-volume-set-for-release-on-october-20 |accessdate=February 10, 2019 |work=[[Crunchyroll]] |date=August 31, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[The Foundation Trilogy]]'' || [[Isaac Asimov]] || English || 3<ref>However further 'Foundation' books were written by Asimov from 1982, extending the direct series to seven books, however these four further novels tell two largely independent stories. Ultimately many of Asimov's works join to form a single time line encompassing 20,000 years of future-history. To further add the extent of the series, a 'Second Foundation Trilogy' of books by contemporary Sci-Fi writers also explicitly join with the series.</ref> || 1950\u20131953 || 20 million<ref>[http://movies.ign.com/articles/036/036229p1.html IGN] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110522132606/http://movies.ign.com/articles/036/036229p1.html |date=2011-05-22 }} 27 June 2000</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Percy Jackson & the Olympians]]'' || [[Rick Riordan]] || English || 5 || 2005\u20132009 || 20 million<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/percy-jackson-problem|title=The Percy Jackson Problem|date=2014-10-22|website=The New Yorker|access-date=2017-01-29|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161126100359/http://www.newyorker.com/culture/cultural-comment/percy-jackson-problem|archivedate=2016-11-26}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Horrible Histories]]'' || 